olive oil
1 carrot
1 courgette
½ Onion
1 packet Beef Rump
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
20 g butter
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Crushed Roasted Cashews
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut carrot and courgette into fries. Cut onion into wedges (see ingredients).
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt. Toss to combine, spread out evenly, then roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.
Little cooks: Help with sprinkling over the seasoning and tossing the veggies!

• While the veggies are roasting, sprinkle the beef rump with Mumbai spice blend, and season with salt and pepper.
• Heat a large frying pan over a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil and the butter.
• When the oil is hot, cook the beef rump for 2-3 minutes on each side (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate to rest for 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, baby spinach leaves, mayonnaise and a drizzle of olive oil in a second medium bowl. Toss to combine. Season to taste

• Slice Mumbai beef rump.
• Divide beef, creamy slaw and roasted veggies between plates.
• Pour over any remaining juices from the pan. Sprinkle over crushed roasted cashews. Serve with Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!